# Flutter Project Rules

Always analyze existing code before generating code.

## Architecture

- Follow Clean Architecture
- Follow Feature First Structure
- Follow existing project conventions

## Reusability

- Reuse existing Theme
- Reuse AppColors
- Reuse AppTextStyles
- Reuse AppDimensions
- Reuse AppSpacing
- Reuse shared widgets
- Reuse extensions and utilities

## Localization

- Never hardcode user-facing strings
- Use AppStrings only
- Add keys in app_strings.dart
- Add English translation in en_us.dart
- Add Hindi translation in hi_in.dart

## Code Quality

- Production-ready code
- Const constructors where possible
- Avoid duplication
- Generate only requested files
- Do not modify unrelated files
